6
00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:02.563
[breathing heavily]

7
00:01:32.802 --> 00:01:33.636
[ring clatters]

8
00:02:00.621 --> 00:02:02.623
♪♪

9
00:02:55.051 --> 00:02:56.469
[thunderclap]

10
00:03:14.320 --> 00:03:16.489
- [man 1 ] What the fuck are you doing?
- [woman screaming]

11
00:03:23.746 --> 00:03:25.122
[woman] Oh. my God!

12
00:03:26.624 --> 00:03:30.378
- [woman screaming] Stop! Stop!
- [man 2 grunting]

13
00:03:30.461 --> 00:03:32.088
[screaming stops]

14
00:03:33.172 --> 00:03:35.007
[grunting]

15
00:03:35.091 --> 00:03:36.509
[liquid sloshing]

16
00:03:49.438 --> 00:03:51.565
[alarm beeping]

17
00:03:51.649 --> 00:03:53.275
[breathing heavily]

18
00:04:06.205 --> 00:04:08.082
[wheezing]

19
00:04:16.424 --> 00:04:18.426
♪♪

20
00:04:37.278 --> 00:04:39.405
[car alarms blaring]

21
00:04:51.292 --> 00:04:53.294
♪♪

22
00:05:01.594 --> 00:05:04.555
- [woman] <i>Good morning to you all.</i>
- [woman 2] <i>Good morning out there.</i>

23
00:05:04.638 --> 00:05:05.890
[woman 3] <i>Good morning to all of you-</i>

24
00:05:05.973 --> 00:05:07.975
[woman 4] <i>On this Monday</i>--
<i>Yeah. it's Monday.</i>

25
00:05:08.058 --> 00:05:09.393
<i>A case of the Mondays.</i>

26
00:05:14.148 --> 00:05:16.567
[man] <i>I am on my third cup of coffee.</i>

27
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:18.027
<i>Anybody else having
a hard time this morning?</i>

28
00:05:18.110 --> 00:05:18.986
[woman] <i>Oh. yeah!</i> [laughter]

29
00:05:22.448 --> 00:05:26.118
[reporter] <i>Drivers are expected
to experience record congestion today.</i>

30
00:05:26.202 --> 00:05:29.663
[reporter 2] <i>Around 100 workers
are losing their jobs.</i>

31
00:05:29.747 --> 00:05:31.624
[woman 5] <i>Are you feeling
stressed out these days?</i>

32
00:05:31.707 --> 00:05:33.334
<i>Hey. guess what? Join the club.</i>

33
00:05:33.417 --> 00:05:34.877
[man 2] <i>Violent altercations can happen</i>

34
00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:38.130
<i>from even the most minor lapses
by drivers.</i>

35
00:05:39.924 --> 00:05:43.052
[woman 6] <i>I've posted every day.
ten times a day. for three years now.</i>

36
00:05:44.053 --> 00:05:46.388
[man 3] <i>Too many people out there
think they can multitask</i>

37
00:05:46.472 --> 00:05:47.806
<i>while operating a vehicle.</i>

38
00:05:51.018 --> 00:05:53.312
[woman 7] <i>Incivility is
a major issue in America.</i>

39
00:05:53.395 --> 00:05:55.272
<i>Rudeness can breed
more rudeness.</i>

40
00:05:55.356 --> 00:05:56.649
[woman 8] <i>We were born angry.</i>

41
00:05:56.732 --> 00:05:59.276
[man 4] <i>And with anger
comes a lack of self-control.</i>

42
00:05:59.360 --> 00:06:02.112
[woman 9] <i>When you're very angry.
you lose a lot of self-control.</i>

43
00:06:04.073 --> 00:06:06.700
[girl] Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

44
00:06:08.827 --> 00:06:10.579
- [man 5] Oh. my--
- Oh. my God.

45
00:06:10.663 --> 00:06:12.206
Oh. my God!

46
00:06:14.416 --> 00:06:16.752
[man 6] <i>Aggressive driving's been
on the rise for several years.</i>

47
00:06:16.835 --> 00:06:19.171
<i>and that's due
to societies moving faster...</i>

48
00:06:19.255 --> 00:06:22.007
[reporter 3] <i>Road-rage fatalities
have skyrocketed 500%.</i>

49
00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:27.721
[reporter 4] <i>A simple ride-share trip
yesterday took a horrific turn.</i>

50
00:06:27.805 --> 00:06:29.932
[woman 10] <i>Local law enforcement
is understaffed</i>

51
00:06:30.015 --> 00:06:31.767
<i>with no new applicants in sight.</i>

52
00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:33.269
[man 7] <i>It's getting real bad out there.</i>

53
00:06:33.352 --> 00:06:34.895
<i>People are taking matters
into their own hands.</i>

54
00:06:34.979 --> 00:06:36.438
[reporter 5] <i>Seeing this live right now.</i>

55
00:06:36.522 --> 00:06:39.024
<i>The police have him cornered-
We're in the middle of a standoff here.</i>

56
00:06:39.108 --> 00:06:40.776
I knew it wasn't going to end well.

57
00:06:41.777 --> 00:06:43.404
[man 8] <i>You gotta
protect yourself these days.</i>

58
00:06:43.487 --> 00:06:44.530
<i>No one else is gonna help you.</i>

59
00:06:44.613 --> 00:06:45.656
Hey! Hey!

60
00:06:45.739 --> 00:06:48.158
[woman on phone] <i>We've been married
15 years. we have three kids.</i>

61
00:06:48.242 --> 00:06:50.619
<i>and my husband's been
cheating on me for years.</i>

62
00:06:50.703 --> 00:06:52.746
[reporter 6] <i>A man who is thought to be
the main suspect...</i>

63
00:06:52.830 --> 00:06:55.624
[man 9] <i>Issues surrounding mental health
are increasing by the day.</i>

64
00:06:55.708 --> 00:06:58.502
[man 10] <i>Inequality is pushing us
farther and farther apart.</i>

65
00:06:58.586 --> 00:07:00.588
[woman 11 ] <i>We are going backwards-</i>

66
00:07:00.671 --> 00:07:03.007
[reporter 7] <i>Thousands of police officers
have been laid off since...</i>

67
00:07:03.090 --> 00:07:04.967
[woman 12] <i>It's a nationwide
epidemic right now.</i>

68
00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:08.262
[reporter 7] <i>It could be years before they
can afford to hire more officers.</i>

69
00:07:08.345 --> 00:07:09.638
[reporter 8] <i>-..searching for a suspect
thought to have...</i>

70
00:07:09.722 --> 00:07:11.724
[reporter 9] <i>Gas prices
were up 82 cents today.</i>

71
00:07:11.807 --> 00:07:13.892
[reporter 10] <i>Ambulance response rates
are slowing down.</i>

72
00:07:13.976 --> 00:07:15.019
[man 11 ] <i>This is a serious issue-</i>

73
00:07:15.102 --> 00:07:16.937
[reporter 10] <i>Stress levels
are at an all-time high.</i>

74
00:07:17.021 --> 00:07:19.356
[reporter 11 ] <i>. -.all the warning signs
of impending collapse.</i>

75
00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:20.649
[reporter 12] <i>Twice as congested
as it would be...</i>

76
00:07:20.733 --> 00:07:22.610
[man 12] <i>When we reach our boiling point
and we explode...</i>

77
00:07:22.693 --> 00:07:24.528
[reporter 13] <i>In the streets
with counter-protestors.</i>

78
00:07:24.612 --> 00:07:26.155
[man 13] <i>We blame the media.
Twitter. Facebook.</i>

79
00:07:26.238 --> 00:07:27.698
<i>We feel all that strain coming out.-.</i>

80
00:07:27.781 --> 00:07:28.949
[reporter 14] <i>It's definitely a problem
that we're facing...</i>

81
00:07:29.033 --> 00:07:30.784
<i>- Takes a toll on your relationships.
- Panic attacks...</i>

82
00:07:30.868 --> 00:07:32.244
<i>- .--your health and well-being-
- Tempers flaring.</i>

83
00:07:32.328 --> 00:07:33.787
[man 14] <i>Why is everything filled
with such garbage?</i>

84
00:07:34.913 --> 00:07:36.665
[woman 13] <i>People have
so much coming at them.</i>

85
00:07:36.749 --> 00:07:38.626
<i>their brains just can't handle it-</i>
[echoing]

86
00:07:45.382 --> 00:07:46.759
[cell phone ringing]

87
00:07:58.395 --> 00:08:00.022
[exhales]

88
00:08:08.489 --> 00:08:10.741
- Andy?
<i>- Hello. You up?</i>

89
00:08:11.784 --> 00:08:13.410
[sighs]

90
00:08:13.494 --> 00:08:14.745
I am now.

91
00:08:14.828 --> 00:08:18.582
<i>Well. that's good. 'cause your soon-to-be
ex filed another motion.</i>

92
00:08:18.666 --> 00:08:20.334
[sighs]

93
00:08:20.417 --> 00:08:21.585
What does he want now?

94
00:08:22.586 --> 00:08:23.545
[Andy grumbles]

95
00:08:24.672 --> 00:08:26.298
Just say it.

96
00:08:26.382 --> 00:08:28.258
<i>He wants the house.</i>

97
00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:32.638
[groans] Of course he does.
[chuckles]

98
00:08:32.721 --> 00:08:34.640
<i>Listen. I'm already
drawing up our objection.</i>

99
00:08:34.723 --> 00:08:35.974
[exhales sharply]

100
00:08:37.184 --> 00:08:40.521
Shit. I didn't set my alarm.

101
00:08:40.604 --> 00:08:44.858
<i>Hey. I just need you
to tell me to file it. okay?</i>

102
00:08:44.942 --> 00:08:47.319
<i>- Rach?</i>
- I need to think about it.

103
00:08:47.403 --> 00:08:49.738
<i>What? Come on.</i>

104
00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:53.242
I just want this to be over.

105
00:08:53.325 --> 00:08:55.744
<i>Rachel. you need to fight this.
and you know that.</i>

106
00:08:55.828 --> 00:08:57.830
<i>Come on. Richard didn't work
for the house. You did.</i>

107
00:08:57.913 --> 00:08:58.872
[footsteps approaching]

108
00:09:00.124 --> 00:09:01.625
Hey. I gotta go.

109
00:09:01.709 --> 00:09:04.670
<i>Okay. but we're continuing
this conversation at lunch.</i>

110
00:09:04.753 --> 00:09:06.171
Yeah. You're the best.

111
00:09:06.255 --> 00:09:07.631
<i>- I know it-</i>
- Bye.

112
00:09:07.715 --> 00:09:08.716
Shouldn't you be dressed?

113
00:09:10.509 --> 00:09:13.804
What. this is not appropriate attire
for your personal chauffeur?

114
00:09:13.887 --> 00:09:16.640
- You have a client.
- No. I don't.

115
00:09:20.227 --> 00:09:22.730
I mean. yes. I do.
But. you know. we're still good.

116
00:09:22.813 --> 00:09:25.232
- It just means we've got--
- Another tardy.

117
00:09:25.315 --> 00:09:26.734
No. we're good.

118
00:09:28.110 --> 00:09:29.528
Okay?

119
00:09:29.611 --> 00:09:33.240
- [man speaking on TV]
- Yeah. No. I know. I-- I get it.

120
00:09:33.323 --> 00:09:35.242
I know you don't like living there.

121
00:09:35.325 --> 00:09:38.996
but it's an assisted-living community.
Mom. it's not an old folks' home.

122
00:09:39.079 --> 00:09:40.456
[inaudible]

123
00:09:40.539 --> 00:09:42.916
Can you hear me? Can you--

124
00:09:44.710 --> 00:09:46.545
Okay. Mom. you need--
I can't hear you.

125
00:09:46.628 --> 00:09:48.881
You need to press
the little microphone button. It's...

126
00:09:48.964 --> 00:09:51.133
<i>.-.firefighters battle
a raging house fire...</i>

127
00:09:51.216 --> 00:09:53.510
Mom. you need to...

128
00:09:53.594 --> 00:09:56.472
You need to press
the little microphone button with the...

129
00:09:56.555 --> 00:10:00.017
I don't know if you can hear me. I'm gonna
come see you later. okay?

130
00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:01.602
- Um... Bye.
- [computer beeps]

131
00:10:01.685 --> 00:10:04.855
[reporter] <i>Police are actively searching
now for the homeowner's ex-husband.</i>

132
00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:08.233
<i>who was last seen fleeing the scene
in a gray pickup truck early this morning.</i>

133
00:10:08.317 --> 00:10:10.319
<i>Our own Pat Davereaux
spoke with a neighbor</i>

134
00:10:10.402 --> 00:10:13.447
<i>about the suspect's history of substance
abuse and violence</i>

135
00:10:13.530 --> 00:10:14.948
<i>after a workplace injury.</i>

136
00:10:15.032 --> 00:10:17.367
<i>She had a restraining order on him.</i>

137
00:10:17.451 --> 00:10:18.535
<i>And now she's gone.</i>

138
00:10:18.619 --> 00:10:20.746
<i>- He just couldn't face it.</i>
- [channel changes]

139
00:10:20.829 --> 00:10:23.123
- I was watching that.
- It's way too early for real life. dude.

140
00:10:23.207 --> 00:10:25.751
Anybody seen
my candy-cane scissors?

141
00:10:25.834 --> 00:10:28.670
Now. why would you
want to cut candy canes?

142
00:10:28.754 --> 00:10:30.964
You know. My scissors with the--

143
00:10:33.675 --> 00:10:34.676
[scoffs] Never mind.

144
00:10:36.845 --> 00:10:39.181
- Is she okay?
- I think so.

145
00:10:41.016 --> 00:10:44.144
- Gonna be late again.
- Found 'em.

146
00:10:44.228 --> 00:10:46.355
Under one of your piles of trash.

147
00:10:46.438 --> 00:10:52.277
Hey. science has proven that piles
are the most efficient filing system.

148
00:10:52.361 --> 00:10:54.112
I read that somewhere.

149
00:10:54.196 --> 00:10:55.489
Those are actually my coupons.

150
00:10:56.490 --> 00:10:58.075
- Were you cutting us coupons?
- Mm-hmm.

151
00:10:58.158 --> 00:11:01.078
- I love you.
- Mm.

152
00:11:01.161 --> 00:11:02.996
Rachel. maybe you could learn
a thing or two from Mary

153
00:11:03.080 --> 00:11:04.581
about fiscal responsibility.

154
00:11:05.624 --> 00:11:06.667
[clears throat]

155
00:11:08.210 --> 00:11:10.963
- Rachel. I-- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

156
00:11:11.046 --> 00:11:12.965
I really love having you
and my brother here.

157
00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:17.761
But if you're so fiscally responsible.

158
00:11:17.844 --> 00:11:19.972
maybe it's time to kick in some rent here.

159
00:11:20.055 --> 00:11:23.058
Rachel. you're the one that said
that we couldn't stay at Mom's.

160
00:11:23.141 --> 00:11:26.228
We need to sell it.
And you know that. Okay?

161
00:11:26.311 --> 00:11:29.648
I can't afford to pay for her care.
and you really can't either.

162
00:11:29.731 --> 00:11:30.732
No. no. I told you.

163
00:11:30.816 --> 00:11:34.736
I'm working on the business
and it's gonna start soon.

164
00:11:34.820 --> 00:11:37.072
Come on. Freddy. we gotta be real.

165
00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:39.032
Real about what?

166
00:11:39.116 --> 00:11:41.201
What does that even mean?

167
00:11:41.285 --> 00:11:43.662
She was getting lost
in her own neighborhood.

168
00:11:43.745 --> 00:11:46.206
But to be fair. I still get
lost in our old neighborhood.

169
00:11:46.290 --> 00:11:49.167
- Even with a phone?
- Yeah.

170
00:11:49.251 --> 00:11:52.296
Yeah. the streets in Linwood Springs are
like a freakin' maze of spaghetti.

171
00:11:52.379 --> 00:11:54.172
Kyle. grab a granola bar.
We gotta go.

172
00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:56.800
I already ate.

173
00:11:56.883 --> 00:11:59.136
Bye. guys. See you after school.

174
00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:01.138
See you. dude.
Blow it up in there.

175
00:12:02.806 --> 00:12:03.807
Bye. buddy.

176
00:12:06.143 --> 00:12:07.728
Morning. Rachel. Hey. Kyle.

177
00:12:07.811 --> 00:12:10.647
Morning. Rosie. New ride?

178
00:12:10.731 --> 00:12:11.857
Yeah. We've gone minivan.

179
00:12:11.940 --> 00:12:13.317
It suits you.

180
00:12:17.279 --> 00:12:18.280
Bye.

181
00:12:22.659 --> 00:12:23.744
[minivan engine starts]

182
00:12:25.037 --> 00:12:26.621
[sighs]

183
00:12:26.705 --> 00:12:28.415
- [engine starts]
- [sighs]

184
00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:30.083
- [dashboard beeps]
- Are we ever gonna get a new ride?

185
00:12:30.167 --> 00:12:31.418
Sure.

186
00:12:33.170 --> 00:12:34.421
You wanna buy me one?

187
00:12:40.635 --> 00:12:44.306
- "Prospective."
- Mom. I'm good.

188
00:12:44.389 --> 00:12:48.477
- Remember. it's not "per-spective."
- "Prospective."

189
00:12:48.560 --> 00:12:54.024
P-R-O-S-P-E-C-T-I-V-E.

190
00:12:54.107 --> 00:12:55.817
- "Prospective."
- Nice job.

191
00:13:03.033 --> 00:13:06.078
Hey. so what do you say?
Should we risk the freeway today?

192
00:13:06.161 --> 00:13:08.246
No. No freeway.

193
00:13:09.373 --> 00:13:12.250
Okay. well. just check
the traffic for me. please.

194
00:13:16.129 --> 00:13:17.589
You don't have a passcode anymore?

195
00:13:17.672 --> 00:13:19.925
Not since I almost crashed
trying to unlock it.

196
00:13:20.008 --> 00:13:21.968
Wow. That's not safe.

197
00:13:24.721 --> 00:13:27.182
- "Precarious."
- What?

198
00:13:27.265 --> 00:13:29.142
Next word. "Precarious."

199
00:13:30.852 --> 00:13:35.857
"Precarious."
P-R-E-C-A-R-I-O-U-S.

200
00:13:35.941 --> 00:13:37.609
- Use it in a sentence.
- Uh...

201
00:13:38.610 --> 00:13:43.573
The way the glass is placed
on the edge of the table is precarious.

202
00:13:43.657 --> 00:13:45.659
Nice. Good job.

203
00:13:47.119 --> 00:13:48.620
Says it's clear.

204
00:13:48.703 --> 00:13:50.914
And that's a problem why?

205
00:13:50.997 --> 00:13:52.624
Because we still can't trust it.

206
00:13:54.167 --> 00:13:55.961
[exhales]

207
00:13:56.044 --> 00:13:59.172
- Sorry. kiddo. but today we must.
- Mom. no!

208
00:13:59.256 --> 00:14:01.299
- I don't have a choice.
- No! Please?

209
00:14:01.383 --> 00:14:03.301
- We're gonna be late.
- Trust me. Kyle.

210
00:14:03.385 --> 00:14:04.970
This is gonna be quicker. okay?

211
00:14:05.053 --> 00:14:07.597
That's what you said the last two times.

212
00:14:12.477 --> 00:14:14.604
Hey. see? All clear.

213
00:14:17.732 --> 00:14:19.276
[cell phone ringing]

214
00:14:19.359 --> 00:14:21.945
It's Dad. Can I please talk to him?

215
00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:22.863
[sighs]

216
00:14:24.865 --> 00:14:26.908
- Hey. Dad.
- [Richard] <i>Hey. man.</i>

217
00:14:26.992 --> 00:14:29.578
Uncle Freddy and I invented
a new <i>Fortnite</i> strategy.

218
00:14:29.661 --> 00:14:31.746
- You wanna hear it?
<i>- Not a good time.</i>

219
00:14:31.830 --> 00:14:33.540
<i>- Maybe later. okay?</i>
- Okay.

220
00:14:33.623 --> 00:14:35.000
You got the tickets
for the game tomorrow?

221
00:14:35.083 --> 00:14:37.252
[scoffs] <i>Yeah. look. about the game-..</i>

222
00:14:37.335 --> 00:14:39.254
<i>My schedule kinda got messed up.</i>

223
00:14:39.337 --> 00:14:41.631
<i>and my boss needs me to go
out of town tomorrow.</i>

224
00:14:41.715 --> 00:14:43.633
<i>- Next time. okay?</i>
- Yeah. okay.

225
00:14:47.762 --> 00:14:49.681
That's really understanding
of you. Kyle.

226
00:14:49.764 --> 00:14:52.058
You know. new jobs.
like your Dad's. can be...

227
00:14:53.310 --> 00:14:55.562
really unpredictable at first.

228
00:14:55.645 --> 00:14:56.730
<i>See? That's right-</i>

229
00:14:56.813 --> 00:15:00.192
<i>But I promise we'll make a plan to go
to a game soon. just as soon as I--</i>

230
00:15:00.275 --> 00:15:02.652
Well. it probably shouldn't be planned.
It should be more a--

231
00:15:02.736 --> 00:15:05.363
a spur-of-the-moment thing. right?

232
00:15:05.447 --> 00:15:10.410
I mean. 'cause plans...
can be hard to stick to.

233
00:15:10.493 --> 00:15:11.578
<i>Yeah. Yeah. yeah.</i>

234
00:15:11.661 --> 00:15:14.789
<i>I just need to keep my new boss happy
so I can get my own place--</i>

235
00:15:14.873 --> 00:15:18.043
Yeah. and maybe stop relying
on other sources of income.

236
00:15:18.126 --> 00:15:21.171
[Richard sighs] <i>Look. I just want
everything to be fair and square. okay?</i>

237
00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:24.216
<i>That's why I called. actually.
I needed to talk to you about moving--</i>

238
00:15:24.299 --> 00:15:26.927
Richard. we gotta go. okay?

239
00:15:27.010 --> 00:15:29.429
We're just getting to school.

240
00:15:29.512 --> 00:15:32.224
<i>Okay. fine. But. you know.
this isn't gonna solve itself.</i>

241
00:15:32.307 --> 00:15:34.768
<i>Look. I'm sorry again. bud-
I'll talk to you soon. okay?</i>

242
00:15:34.851 --> 00:15:37.604
- Okay.
<i>- Okay. All right. Bye.</i>

243
00:15:37.687 --> 00:15:39.814
- [line clicks]
- Bye.

244
00:15:39.898 --> 00:15:40.899
Bye.

245
00:15:46.112 --> 00:15:48.740
I am... I'm sorry. Kyle.

246
00:15:50.283 --> 00:15:51.201
[sighs]

247
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:01.169
Three tardies is an automatic detention.

248
00:16:03.296 --> 00:16:05.173
I'm doing the best I can here. Okay?

249
00:16:08.927 --> 00:16:11.513
[groans] Seriously?

250
00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:19.604
[horns honking]

251
00:16:19.688 --> 00:16:20.689
I can't believe this.

252
00:16:22.274 --> 00:16:24.276
[cell phone ringing]

253
00:16:27.237 --> 00:16:28.738
Deborah's calling you.

254
00:16:30.699 --> 00:16:31.950
[ringing continues]

255
00:16:37.956 --> 00:16:40.834
Deborah. Hey. I was just gonna call you.

256
00:16:40.917 --> 00:16:44.212
<i>I just wanted to make sure
I was gonna see you at 9:00.</i>

257
00:16:44.296 --> 00:16:46.756
- Absolutely.
<i>- Oh. great. I have a big day today.</i>

258
00:16:46.840 --> 00:16:49.968
Uh... but I've just hit hellish traffic.

259
00:16:50.051 --> 00:16:53.972
so I'm gonna be 15.
maybe 20 minutes late. tops.

260
00:16:54.055 --> 00:16:56.850
<i>Are you serious?</i>

261
00:16:56.933 --> 00:17:00.937
Actually. you know what?
It looks like it might be clearing. so...

262
00:17:02.397 --> 00:17:03.398
We're good.

263
00:17:03.481 --> 00:17:05.984
[sighs] <i>I can't do this again. Rachel.</i>

264
00:17:06.067 --> 00:17:09.487
<i>You know what? I'm gonna call Linda's guy
and get in there.</i>

265
00:17:09.571 --> 00:17:12.657
<i>I love you. Rachel.
but ever since you lost your salon--</i>

266
00:17:12.741 --> 00:17:15.910
<i>I can't believe I'm gonna say this.
but you're fired. Get your shit together.</i>

267
00:17:15.994 --> 00:17:18.747
- Deborah. no. wait. I'm sorry. okay?
- [line clicks]

268
00:17:18.830 --> 00:17:20.832
♪♪

269
00:17:22.208 --> 00:17:23.501
Oh. my God.

270
00:17:24.961 --> 00:17:26.588
Are you okay. Mom?

271
00:17:27.714 --> 00:17:28.757
Yeah.

272
00:17:29.966 --> 00:17:30.884
Just...

273
00:17:31.885 --> 00:17:35.055
Oh. my God. Just my...

274
00:17:35.138 --> 00:17:36.765
My best client. that's all.

275
00:17:38.058 --> 00:17:39.309
I'm sorry.

276
00:17:44.522 --> 00:17:45.565
[exhales]

277
00:17:45.648 --> 00:17:47.275
Eight miles. you know. That's it.

278
00:17:49.027 --> 00:17:52.864
What takes ten minutes on a Sunday.
takes an hour every other day...

279
00:17:54.115 --> 00:17:57.369
and wrecks your career. You know why?

280
00:18:02.040 --> 00:18:03.041
Too many cars.

281
00:18:03.124 --> 00:18:07.379
Too many cars and too many people.

282
00:18:07.462 --> 00:18:09.547
Didn't you also oversleep?

283
00:18:13.885 --> 00:18:15.845
Yes. Yes.

284
00:18:17.138 --> 00:18:20.433
And I overslept.
You're absolutely right.

285
00:18:20.517 --> 00:18:21.476
[chuckles]

286
00:18:23.186 --> 00:18:24.187
It's okay.

287
00:18:28.566 --> 00:18:29.734
So...

288
00:18:31.403 --> 00:18:33.113
any suggestions?

289
00:18:33.196 --> 00:18:35.698
You could take the next exit
and do surface streets.

290
00:18:39.828 --> 00:18:40.912
You got it.

291
00:18:40.995 --> 00:18:43.748
Hold on. I'm gonna get us out of this.

292
00:18:45.041 --> 00:18:47.252
[horns honking]

293
00:18:47.335 --> 00:18:50.004
From now on.
no more freeways. okay?

294
00:18:50.088 --> 00:18:54.008
I only trust you. okay? Deal?

295
00:18:54.092 --> 00:18:55.218
Deal.

296
00:19:00.432 --> 00:19:02.976
[horns continue honking]

297
00:19:18.491 --> 00:19:19.325
[Rachel sighs]

298
00:19:19.409 --> 00:19:21.411
♪♪

299
00:19:46.811 --> 00:19:48.229
[sighs]

300
00:19:48.313 --> 00:19:51.024
It's not getting any greener.

301
00:19:51.107 --> 00:19:52.442
Come on. man.

302
00:19:52.525 --> 00:19:54.277
Come on!

303
00:19:54.360 --> 00:19:55.236
[growls]

304
00:19:55.320 --> 00:19:56.487
[horn blares]

305
00:19:56.571 --> 00:19:58.448
Go!

306
00:19:58.531 --> 00:20:00.533
[breathes deeply]

307
00:20:00.617 --> 00:20:02.660
[horn blares]

308
00:20:02.744 --> 00:20:03.995
[groans]

309
00:20:09.209 --> 00:20:11.502
[horn blares]

310
00:20:11.586 --> 00:20:12.837
[tires squeal]

311
00:20:18.551 --> 00:20:21.137
[sighs] No. no. Go.

312
00:20:22.222 --> 00:20:24.265
Oh. come on.

313
00:20:25.266 --> 00:20:26.851
Of course. Yeah.

314
00:20:26.935 --> 00:20:28.937
♪♪

315
00:20:48.748 --> 00:20:50.375
- Kyle. don't.
- Morning.

316
00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:54.295
I don't even get a courtesy tap first?

317
00:20:54.379 --> 00:20:55.922
Roll up your window.

318
00:21:00.843 --> 00:21:02.345
It's not working.

319
00:21:02.428 --> 00:21:05.181
You know what
a courtesy tap is. young man?

320
00:21:05.265 --> 00:21:06.808
Just ignore him.

321
00:21:09.143 --> 00:21:10.603
Sounds like this.

322
00:21:10.687 --> 00:21:13.648
- [three short honks]
- It's light. It's friendly.

323
00:21:13.731 --> 00:21:16.442
Just like you're trying to get
somebody's attention.

324
00:21:16.526 --> 00:21:18.987
I'm sure that's what your mom meant.

325
00:21:19.070 --> 00:21:20.780
Is that right. ma'am?

326
00:21:20.863 --> 00:21:23.574
- Is a courtesy tap what you meant?
- No. it's not.

327
00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:27.120
Why is that?

328
00:21:27.203 --> 00:21:29.914
The light was green.
and you weren't moving.

329
00:21:29.998 --> 00:21:32.834
Mom. Stop it. please.

330
00:21:32.917 --> 00:21:34.919
Some of us have places to be.

331
00:21:37.171 --> 00:21:39.841
Yeah. I admit to being
a little zoned out back there.

332
00:21:42.510 --> 00:21:44.971
I've been kind of having
a hard time lately.

333
00:21:45.054 --> 00:21:47.098
Yeah. well. join the club.

334
00:21:47.181 --> 00:21:50.101
- [whispering] Stop it.
- Well. I'm sorry.

335
00:21:52.186 --> 00:21:56.691
I'm sorry that you are. and I'm sorry
that... I might've made it worse.

336
00:21:58.735 --> 00:22:00.236
You accept my apology?

337
00:22:01.696 --> 00:22:04.407
- Sure. whatever.
- Perfect.

338
00:22:06.034 --> 00:22:08.661
If you could just do the same.
we could press reset.

339
00:22:09.704 --> 00:22:12.081
Ma'am. I was saying.
if you could just apologize--

340
00:22:12.165 --> 00:22:13.166
Yeah. I heard you.

341
00:22:14.917 --> 00:22:16.085
And?

342
00:22:16.169 --> 00:22:18.755
I don't have anything
to apologize for. sir.

343
00:22:18.838 --> 00:22:21.299
- Mom. Just apologize.
- It's okay.

344
00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:25.261
Well. I don't think that's really true
of any of us now. is it?

345
00:22:27.138 --> 00:22:29.140
But that's where we are
in this world today.

346
00:22:30.475 --> 00:22:33.895
We seem to have developed
a fundamental inability to apologize

347
00:22:33.978 --> 00:22:36.522
to anyone. for anything.

348
00:22:42.612 --> 00:22:45.198
I don't even think you really know
what a bad day is.

349
00:22:49.535 --> 00:22:50.912
But you're gonna find out.

350
00:22:52.789 --> 00:22:54.040
You hear me. miss?

351
00:22:55.208 --> 00:22:57.043
You're gonna fucking learn.

352
00:22:57.126 --> 00:22:59.128
♪♪

353
00:23:02.965 --> 00:23:04.884
Hey. can you go. please?

354
00:23:04.967 --> 00:23:06.219
Just go.

355
00:23:30.701 --> 00:23:31.619
Shit.

356
00:23:36.624 --> 00:23:37.583
Mom.

357
00:23:41.629 --> 00:23:43.673
- [Kyle] Oh. my gosh! Stop!
- [tires squeal]

358
00:23:45.049 --> 00:23:47.051
♪♪

359
00:23:49.804 --> 00:23:50.805
Are you okay?

360
00:23:51.889 --> 00:23:53.015
Yeah.

361
00:23:53.099 --> 00:23:54.892
What's this guy's problem?

362
00:23:54.976 --> 00:23:56.894
- [chuckles]
- [engine revs]

363
00:23:56.978 --> 00:23:59.272
- [tires squeal]
- [horn honks]

364
00:24:15.037 --> 00:24:16.497
[horns honking]

365
00:24:17.582 --> 00:24:18.958
[Kyle] What's he doing?

366
00:24:19.041 --> 00:24:20.710
[Rachel] Just gonna let
this person go on his way

367
00:24:20.793 --> 00:24:23.045
- and take the back way. okay?
- Okay.

368
00:24:23.129 --> 00:24:25.047
[engine revving]

369
00:24:26.716 --> 00:24:28.759
- Come on. come on. come on.
- [Kyle] Is he stopping?

370
00:24:28.843 --> 00:24:30.178
Come on.

371
00:24:30.261 --> 00:24:31.471
[honking continues]

372
00:24:33.681 --> 00:24:35.057
[tires squeal]

373
00:24:38.311 --> 00:24:39.645
Come on.

374
00:24:47.236 --> 00:24:48.237
[Rachel exhales]

375
00:24:49.697 --> 00:24:51.491
So that was terrifying.

376
00:24:53.659 --> 00:24:57.914
You know. some people are just jerks.
and that's all there is to it.

377
00:25:00.124 --> 00:25:01.501
Everything's gonna be okay.

378
00:25:03.211 --> 00:25:04.754
I got the window up.

379
00:25:10.092 --> 00:25:11.469
[Rachel clears throat]

380
00:25:13.679 --> 00:25:15.640
Hey. So...

381
00:25:15.723 --> 00:25:19.185
What was that <i>Fortnite</i> strategy
you and Uncle Freddy came up with?

382
00:25:21.312 --> 00:25:22.647
You don't care about that.

383
00:25:22.730 --> 00:25:25.983
Of course I do. I wanna learn.

384
00:25:26.067 --> 00:25:27.360
I wanna learn.

385
00:25:29.570 --> 00:25:31.822
You play duos and glide down to a place

386
00:25:31.906 --> 00:25:34.116
you're really familiar with.
like Retail Row.

387
00:25:34.200 --> 00:25:36.035
And then. one of you distracts an enemy

388
00:25:36.118 --> 00:25:38.996
while the other speeds a golf cart
out from a hiding place

389
00:25:39.080 --> 00:25:40.748
and crashes into them.

390
00:25:44.085 --> 00:25:45.962
You don't even know
what I'm talking about.

391
00:25:46.963 --> 00:25:50.383
You're right. I don't.
but it sounds awesome.

392
00:25:51.634 --> 00:25:53.010
Seriously.

393
00:26:00.810 --> 00:26:01.894
[school bell rings]

394
00:26:01.978 --> 00:26:03.980
[bell tolling]

395
00:26:19.829 --> 00:26:20.913
So...

396
00:26:22.331 --> 00:26:23.708
how long's detention?

397
00:26:23.791 --> 00:26:26.168
Thirty minutes.

398
00:26:26.252 --> 00:26:30.590
Okay. so I'll bail you out
3:30 on the nose. and I'll even have

399
00:26:30.673 --> 00:26:36.596
a big. "make it up to you"
Butterfinger Blizzard ready and waiting.

400
00:26:37.722 --> 00:26:38.973
I promise.

401
00:26:40.141 --> 00:26:41.684
You don't have to promise.

402
00:26:41.767 --> 00:26:42.977
Kyle.

403
00:26:44.395 --> 00:26:46.689
Can you please try to be on time?

404
00:26:46.772 --> 00:26:48.232
Yeah. of course.

405
00:26:55.072 --> 00:26:56.115
[sighs]

406
00:27:11.797 --> 00:27:13.966
[line ringing]

407
00:27:17.136 --> 00:27:19.513
<i>- Rach?</i>
- My nine o'clock fired--

408
00:27:19.597 --> 00:27:21.015
- [horn blares]
- [tires squeal]

409
00:27:24.018 --> 00:27:26.020
...fired me. [sighs] Hey. you...

410
00:27:27.438 --> 00:27:28.689
You still there?

411
00:27:28.773 --> 00:27:30.441
<i>Uh. yeah. What happened?</i>

412
00:27:30.524 --> 00:27:32.610
Oh. God.

413
00:27:32.693 --> 00:27:36.447
The freeway was a parking lot.
and my biggest client couldn't wait.

414
00:27:36.530 --> 00:27:40.326
- so she told me to go to hell.
<i>- That sucks.</i>

415
00:27:40.409 --> 00:27:43.663
Yeah. and then some psycho flipped out
on me and Kyle driving to school.

416
00:27:45.247 --> 00:27:47.625
<i>- And all this before noon. Shit-</i>
- [chuckles] Yeah.

417
00:27:47.708 --> 00:27:49.460
<i>At least the day can't get any worse. huh?</i>

418
00:27:49.543 --> 00:27:53.839
Yeah. I could really use some therapy
on top of the legal advice.

419
00:27:53.923 --> 00:27:55.466
Can you do breakfast instead?

420
00:27:55.549 --> 00:27:58.010
<i>Um.-. at Darrow's?</i>

421
00:27:58.094 --> 00:28:00.971
Yes. Pancake therapy. even better.

422
00:28:01.055 --> 00:28:02.556
Twenty minutes?

423
00:28:02.640 --> 00:28:05.101
<i>Mm. "Human" 20 minutes.
or "Rachel" 20 minutes?</i>

424
00:28:05.184 --> 00:28:07.895
Ha. ha. See you in 20.

425
00:28:07.978 --> 00:28:09.313
[phone alert chimes]

426
00:28:11.232 --> 00:28:12.483
[chuckles]

427
00:28:16.362 --> 00:28:17.488
[sighs]

428
00:28:31.252 --> 00:28:32.628
[sets parking brake]

429
00:28:44.849 --> 00:28:46.308
[card reader beeps]

430
00:28:57.945 --> 00:28:59.905
- [music playing over speakers]
- [cashier] Thank you.

431
00:28:59.989 --> 00:29:01.323
- Thank you.
- [door chimes]

432
00:29:07.997 --> 00:29:09.373
[beeping]

433
00:29:14.795 --> 00:29:16.630
[door chimes]

434
00:29:20.718 --> 00:29:21.802
[cashier] Thank you.

435
00:29:23.804 --> 00:29:25.389
Cash or credit?

436
00:29:25.473 --> 00:29:27.600
That'll be. uh. $5.33.

437
00:29:27.683 --> 00:29:29.935
- Okay. Thank you.
- Hi.

438
00:29:30.019 --> 00:29:33.105
Can I have five Powerball
Quick Picks? Thanks.

439
00:29:33.189 --> 00:29:34.148
And those.

440
00:29:35.566 --> 00:29:38.319
That'll be $13.31.

441
00:29:42.114 --> 00:29:43.240
Out of 20...

442
00:29:43.324 --> 00:29:44.783
Here are your tickets.

443
00:29:46.202 --> 00:29:48.037
- Here's your change.
- Thanks.

444
00:29:51.790 --> 00:29:52.875
Okay. Thank you.

445
00:29:52.958 --> 00:29:55.461
♪♪

446
00:29:55.544 --> 00:29:57.046
What can I get you. sir?

447
00:29:57.129 --> 00:29:59.965
- Just a pack of Ventti gold.
- That'll be all?

448
00:30:01.550 --> 00:30:03.427
- That's it.
- All right. Cash or credit?

449
00:30:05.054 --> 00:30:06.388
Okay.

450
00:30:06.472 --> 00:30:07.932
[chime plays]

451
00:30:13.896 --> 00:30:15.314
Hi.

452
00:30:17.608 --> 00:30:19.485
Uh. ma'am. are you okay?

453
00:30:19.568 --> 00:30:21.195
Yeah. Uh...

454
00:30:24.323 --> 00:30:26.283
Actually. no. I...

455
00:30:26.367 --> 00:30:29.245
I'm pretty sure the guy in that truck's
following me.

456
00:30:29.328 --> 00:30:32.206
- He somebody you know?
- No. we...

457
00:30:32.289 --> 00:30:34.917
we kind of exchanged words
at an intersection.

458
00:30:35.000 --> 00:30:37.044
I honked my horn at him. and now he's--

459
00:30:37.127 --> 00:30:39.171
He's road-raging you.

460
00:30:39.255 --> 00:30:41.131
You could say that.

461
00:30:41.215 --> 00:30:42.967
- You want me to call the cops?
- Nah. that'll take all day.

462
00:30:43.050 --> 00:30:44.802
Besides. that'll just
piss him off even more.

463
00:30:44.885 --> 00:30:46.303
Might. Might not.

464
00:30:46.387 --> 00:30:48.389
Look. I can call 'em.

465
00:30:48.472 --> 00:30:50.307
I don't know. I'm probably
just being paranoid.

466
00:30:50.391 --> 00:30:52.476
How 'bout I walk out with you?

467
00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:54.937
- You don't have to do that.
- I'm heading out there anyway.

468
00:30:56.480 --> 00:30:59.024
- So. you think he's--
- He's just trying to scare you.

469
00:30:59.108 --> 00:31:01.235
If he sees both of us together.
and he doesn't drive off.

470
00:31:01.318 --> 00:31:02.820
you still get in your car.

471
00:31:02.903 --> 00:31:04.238
I make sure I get his plates.

472
00:31:04.321 --> 00:31:06.865
If he follows you out.
we'll all call the cops.

473
00:31:07.992 --> 00:31:11.203
Okay. Thanks. I appreciate it.

474
00:31:13.872 --> 00:31:15.874
♪♪

475
00:31:32.933 --> 00:31:35.519
Why don't you just get in the car?
I'm gonna grab his plates.

476
00:31:45.362 --> 00:31:47.364
♪♪

477
00:31:49.199 --> 00:31:51.285
7-11 -TPX.

478
00:31:52.286 --> 00:31:54.246
7-1 -1 -TPX.

479
00:31:54.330 --> 00:31:55.456
Thanks.

480
00:31:59.793 --> 00:32:00.753
[man] Hey.

481
00:32:01.754 --> 00:32:03.922
Why don't you just chill. man?
Go your own way.

482
00:32:09.762 --> 00:32:11.388
[engine starts]

483
00:32:19.605 --> 00:32:21.273
It's a smart move staying put. bro.

484
