<i>Sorry. Rachel.</i>

982
01:00:49.938 --> 01:00:51.815
<i>Freddy's gone.</i>

983
01:00:51.899 --> 01:00:53.275
<i>If it's any consolation.</i>

984
01:00:53.359 --> 01:00:55.652
a fucking cop shot my shoulder up.

985
01:00:55.736 --> 01:00:59.698
- I hope you bleed to death.
<i>- Well. that was sincere.</i>

986
01:00:59.782 --> 01:01:01.992
It's just not an apology.

987
01:01:02.076 --> 01:01:05.204
There are a lot of people
in my life who deserve apologies.

988
01:01:05.287 --> 01:01:06.455
You are not one of them.

989
01:01:09.041 --> 01:01:11.293
Let's talk about Kyle

990
01:01:11.377 --> 01:01:13.379
<i>and how he's gonna die.</i>

991
01:01:15.089 --> 01:01:17.299
You so much as breathe in his direction.

992
01:01:17.383 --> 01:01:19.760
no force on this earth
will stop me from killing you.

993
01:01:19.843 --> 01:01:22.971
<i>. Do you hear me?</i>
- Sounds like you're waking up!

994
01:01:23.055 --> 01:01:26.058
I am wide awake.

995
01:01:26.141 --> 01:01:28.769
<i>Wide awake!</i>

996
01:01:28.852 --> 01:01:32.106
That's good.
'cause we ain't near done yet.

997
01:01:32.189 --> 01:01:33.982
- [grunts]
- Yes. this is over.

998
01:01:34.066 --> 01:01:36.610
This is so fucking over. you sick fuck!

999
01:01:38.362 --> 01:01:40.239
[gasps. panting]

1000
01:01:42.574 --> 01:01:43.826
Where should we go?

1001
01:01:44.993 --> 01:01:47.246
Police station. We should
go to the police station.

1002
01:01:47.413 --> 01:01:49.331
♪♪

1003
01:01:58.799 --> 01:01:59.967
Mom?

1004
01:02:01.093 --> 01:02:02.219
Yeah?

1005
01:02:02.302 --> 01:02:04.012
Can I call Dad?

1006
01:02:05.472 --> 01:02:08.225
Sweetie. I don't have
my phone. remember?

1007
01:02:08.308 --> 01:02:09.935
That man took it.

1008
01:02:11.395 --> 01:02:12.521
You have your tablet?

1009
01:02:15.607 --> 01:02:17.234
I think he stole it too.

1010
01:02:17.317 --> 01:02:19.278
Well. that's probably a good thing.

1011
01:02:20.779 --> 01:02:22.448
Well... he has your phone.

1012
01:02:22.531 --> 01:02:25.826
so if we had your tablet.
he could know where we are.

1013
01:02:26.869 --> 01:02:27.744
What?

1014
01:02:29.037 --> 01:02:31.165
He did know where we were. but...

1015
01:02:31.248 --> 01:02:32.875
he was using that flip phone.

1016
01:02:33.876 --> 01:02:35.002
Don't you think?

1017
01:02:36.003 --> 01:02:38.046
Yeah. maybe.

1018
01:02:39.423 --> 01:02:40.507
Hey. um...

1019
01:02:42.092 --> 01:02:44.303
I looked for my tablet before. but...

1020
01:02:44.386 --> 01:02:45.888
do you just wanna take another look
around. just in case?

1021
01:02:45.971 --> 01:02:47.890
- Yeah.
- [seatbelt clicks]

1022
01:02:49.391 --> 01:02:50.726
- Check the seat pockets.
- Okay.

1023
01:02:51.977 --> 01:02:53.395
Have a really good look. okay?

1024
01:02:57.024 --> 01:02:58.192
Look under the seats.

1025
01:03:00.986 --> 01:03:02.779
- You see it?
- I don't think it's in here.

1026
01:03:06.617 --> 01:03:09.286
Wait. I think I feel something.

1027
01:03:11.038 --> 01:03:12.831
- I think I see it.
- Where?

1028
01:03:12.915 --> 01:03:15.000
- Under your seat. it's...
- What?

1029
01:03:15.083 --> 01:03:17.377
- It's stuck. It--
- It's what?

1030
01:03:17.461 --> 01:03:19.505
[grunts] It was taped.

1031
01:03:20.672 --> 01:03:22.132
Oh. my God.

1032
01:03:22.216 --> 01:03:23.550
Should I throw it out the window?

1033
01:03:23.634 --> 01:03:26.220
- Yeah. No.
- What?

1034
01:03:26.303 --> 01:03:27.387
Wait. wait. wait.

1035
01:03:27.471 --> 01:03:29.348
- "Find Your Phone" app.
- Yeah?

1036
01:03:29.431 --> 01:03:33.018
- You put it on the tablet too?
- Yeah.

1037
01:03:33.101 --> 01:03:37.648
So. if he still has my phone.
we should be able to track him. right?

1038
01:03:37.731 --> 01:03:39.441
Right.

1039
01:03:39.525 --> 01:03:41.610
- Is it working?
- [tablet beeps]

1040
01:03:42.945 --> 01:03:44.780
- [tablet beeps]
- I see it.

1041
01:03:44.863 --> 01:03:45.864
Where is it?

1042
01:03:47.032 --> 01:03:48.033
Right next to us.

1043
01:03:49.743 --> 01:03:51.078
Oh. my God.

1044
01:03:53.038 --> 01:03:54.206
Do you see him?

1045
01:03:54.289 --> 01:03:56.291
♪♪

1046
01:04:02.339 --> 01:04:03.340
Oh. my God.

1047
01:04:05.676 --> 01:04:07.219
He's in front of us.

1048
01:04:07.302 --> 01:04:09.930
- He is?
- He has Rosie's van.

1049
01:04:11.557 --> 01:04:13.892
Mom. look! There's a cop.

1050
01:04:15.602 --> 01:04:17.354
- Do you see him?
- It's okay. It's gonna be okay.

1051
01:04:17.437 --> 01:04:19.273
He can help us.

1052
01:04:19.356 --> 01:04:21.024
Put your seatbelt back on.

1053
01:04:24.695 --> 01:04:27.906
- Do not look at him. okay?
- Okay.

1054
01:04:27.990 --> 01:04:29.992
♪♪

1055
01:04:53.015 --> 01:04:56.059
- Mom. that-- that was--
- The exit. I know. I know.

1056
01:04:56.143 --> 01:04:59.354
Kyle. just trust me
and get his attention.

1057
01:04:59.438 --> 01:05:01.356
Officer!

1058
01:05:01.440 --> 01:05:03.150
Hey!

1059
01:05:03.233 --> 01:05:05.027
- Officer! Help!
- Hello!

1060
01:05:05.110 --> 01:05:07.654
- Officer! Hey!
- Hey! Help!

1061
01:05:10.240 --> 01:05:11.742
Roll your window down!

1062
01:05:11.825 --> 01:05:14.786
- Please help us! Hello. hey!
- We need help!

1063
01:05:14.870 --> 01:05:17.247
The guy you're looking for.
he's behind you!

1064
01:05:17.331 --> 01:05:18.457
Right behind you!

1065
01:05:20.834 --> 01:05:21.877
Please help us!

1066
01:05:21.960 --> 01:05:22.836
Pull over!

1067
01:05:22.919 --> 01:05:23.754
[crash]

1068
01:05:29.301 --> 01:05:30.886
[panting]

1069
01:05:30.969 --> 01:05:32.095
Dispatch. request assist--

1070
01:05:33.513 --> 01:05:34.431
[gasps]

1071
01:05:34.514 --> 01:05:37.017
♪♪

1072
01:05:40.979 --> 01:05:42.606
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1073
01:05:42.689 --> 01:05:44.691
♪♪

1074
01:05:49.196 --> 01:05:51.615
- Can you see him?
- He's catching up.

1075
01:05:53.950 --> 01:05:55.952
Go! Go!

1076
01:05:56.036 --> 01:05:57.496
Kyle. call 911 on the tablet.

1077
01:05:57.579 --> 01:05:59.081
- [beeping]
- [line ringing]

1078
01:06:01.041 --> 01:06:02.542
[operator] <i>911.
What's your emergency?</i>

1079
01:06:02.626 --> 01:06:05.879
The man on the news.
he's chasing me in a silver minivan.

1080
01:06:05.962 --> 01:06:07.798
<i>. Your current location?</i>
- Driving on 95 south.

1081
01:06:07.881 --> 01:06:09.257
just after the State exit.

1082
01:06:09.341 --> 01:06:10.801
<i>Ma'am. all units in that vicinity</i>

1083
01:06:10.884 --> 01:06:13.553
<i>Are currently responding
to a multi-vehicle crash.</i>

1084
01:06:13.637 --> 01:06:15.305
He caused that accident!

1085
01:06:15.389 --> 01:06:16.848
My son and I are in danger.

1086
01:06:16.932 --> 01:06:18.517
<i>Ma'am. we cannot
get to you at the moment.</i>

1087
01:06:18.600 --> 01:06:21.103
<i>Stay on the line.
get some place safe. and--</i>

1088
01:06:21.186 --> 01:06:23.438
- Mom. it died!
- Shit.

1089
01:06:23.522 --> 01:06:24.606
Shit. shit. shit. shit.

1090
01:06:25.899 --> 01:06:26.942
Tell me you have the charger.

1091
01:06:28.485 --> 01:06:30.237
I don't. Oh. my God.

1092
01:06:31.238 --> 01:06:32.447
We're on our own.

1093
01:06:32.531 --> 01:06:34.449
Okay. Okay.

1094
01:06:34.533 --> 01:06:36.410
[Kyle] We should just go to the station.

1095
01:06:36.493 --> 01:06:39.371
[Rachel] There's no way we can outrun him.
We have to lose him.

1096
01:06:39.454 --> 01:06:41.832
- We need to go to Grandma's.
- Why?

1097
01:06:41.915 --> 01:06:43.250
It's your strategy. remember?

1098
01:06:43.333 --> 01:06:44.710
- From the videogame?
- What?

1099
01:06:44.793 --> 01:06:46.336
It's somewhere we're familiar with. okay?

1100
01:06:47.754 --> 01:06:50.215
It's the safest place to hide you.

1101
01:06:50.298 --> 01:06:52.884
And we can call for help
with the silent alarm.

1102
01:06:52.968 --> 01:06:55.470
and it'll confuse the heck out of someone
who's never been there before.

1103
01:06:55.554 --> 01:06:58.140
Right. like Uncle Freddy was saying.

1104
01:06:58.223 --> 01:07:00.726
He'd still get lost there.
like in a maze of spaghetti.

1105
01:07:00.809 --> 01:07:02.144
Yeah. exactly.

1106
01:07:02.227 --> 01:07:04.896
- So you think he'll get lost?
- For long enough.

1107
01:07:04.980 --> 01:07:06.773
[panting]

1108
01:07:06.857 --> 01:07:08.859
♪♪

1109
01:07:13.947 --> 01:07:15.449
[Rachel panting]

1110
01:07:19.953 --> 01:07:20.996
Drive!

1111
01:07:21.079 --> 01:07:22.748
Go faster! Speed up!

1112
01:07:22.831 --> 01:07:24.833
♪♪

1113
01:08:06.458 --> 01:08:08.210
[grunting]

1114
01:08:11.338 --> 01:08:13.340
♪♪

1115
01:08:23.183 --> 01:08:24.518
He's right behind us.

1116
01:08:25.769 --> 01:08:26.895
He's catching up.

1117
01:08:29.898 --> 01:08:31.900
♪♪

1118
01:08:37.405 --> 01:08:38.532
Can you go any faster?

1119
01:08:41.117 --> 01:08:42.285
[tires squealing]

1120
01:08:51.336 --> 01:08:52.963
[horns honking]

1121
01:08:55.632 --> 01:08:57.634
♪♪

1122
01:09:04.724 --> 01:09:06.268
[panting]

1123
01:09:06.351 --> 01:09:08.353
[engine revs]

1124
01:09:14.860 --> 01:09:15.694
Hold on!

1125
01:09:15.777 --> 01:09:17.737
- [brakes screech]
- [tires squeal]

1126
01:09:25.078 --> 01:09:25.996
[grunts]

1127
01:09:39.009 --> 01:09:40.844
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

1128
01:09:43.138 --> 01:09:44.598
[labored breathing]

1129
01:09:46.558 --> 01:09:47.684
[groans]

1130
01:09:54.190 --> 01:09:56.192
♪♪

1131
01:09:56.276 --> 01:09:58.612
- Can you see him?
- No.

1132
01:09:58.695 --> 01:10:00.155
I think he's still back
towards the entrance.

1133
01:10:00.238 --> 01:10:02.240
♪♪

1134
01:10:56.753 --> 01:10:57.796
Kyle.

1135
01:10:59.422 --> 01:11:01.466
Starting now. we stick to our plan.

1136
01:11:01.549 --> 01:11:02.926
Our backup plan.

1137
01:11:03.009 --> 01:11:06.596
Yeah. if we do that. I promise you...

1138
01:11:06.680 --> 01:11:09.849
We're gonna get through this together.
okay? You and me.

1139
01:11:09.933 --> 01:11:11.226
- Yeah.
- Okay?

1140
01:11:15.313 --> 01:11:17.023
Go. Go.

1141
01:11:17.107 --> 01:11:19.109
♪♪

1142
01:11:23.113 --> 01:11:24.072
[beeps]

1143
01:11:25.699 --> 01:11:27.075
[panting]

1144
01:11:31.705 --> 01:11:32.747
[beeps]

1145
01:11:47.679 --> 01:11:49.681
♪♪

1146
01:12:43.359 --> 01:12:45.361
[breathing hard]

1147
01:12:52.577 --> 01:12:54.496
♪♪

1148
01:13:22.398 --> 01:13:24.067
- [breathing heavily]
- [pills rattle]

1149
01:13:40.333 --> 01:13:41.334
[exhales]

1150
01:13:54.097 --> 01:13:56.099
- [gasping. coughing]
- [engine hissing]

1151
01:14:13.116 --> 01:14:14.075
- [growls]
- [yelps]

1152
01:14:16.953 --> 01:14:19.497
- [panting]
- Look at me! Look at me!

1153
01:14:19.581 --> 01:14:23.251
Look at me. You see me?
You're always gonna see me.

1154
01:14:24.252 --> 01:14:28.882
I'm always gonna be inside your head.
every time you think of your little boy...

1155
01:14:29.883 --> 01:14:33.094
and what you could've done to save him.

1156
01:14:34.304 --> 01:14:35.305
[grunts]

1157
01:14:36.973 --> 01:14:38.308
[panting]

1158
01:14:39.893 --> 01:14:41.895
♪♪

1159
01:14:57.577 --> 01:14:59.579
[breathing heavily]

1160
01:15:12.592 --> 01:15:13.468
Kyle?

1161
01:15:15.386 --> 01:15:16.429
Kyle Flynn?

1162
01:15:18.681 --> 01:15:19.891
It's the police.

1163
01:15:21.434 --> 01:15:23.019
You're safe. son. Come on out.

1164
01:15:26.439 --> 01:15:27.440
Come on. son.

1165
01:15:37.992 --> 01:15:41.204
Your mom's hurt. but she's okay.

1166
01:15:43.623 --> 01:15:45.375
She asked us to come and get you.

1167
01:15:45.458 --> 01:15:47.460
♪♪

1168
01:15:52.590 --> 01:15:54.384
[breathing heavily]

1169
01:15:59.931 --> 01:16:01.933
[sirens blaring]

1170
01:16:06.229 --> 01:16:09.440
Come on. son. It's okay.

1171
01:16:14.529 --> 01:16:15.697
Come on out. boy.

1172
01:16:21.244 --> 01:16:22.787
[breathing heavily]

1173
01:16:23.788 --> 01:16:25.373
[clanking]

1174
01:16:25.456 --> 01:16:27.458
♪♪

1175
01:16:41.973 --> 01:16:44.100
[screams]

1176
01:16:44.183 --> 01:16:45.560
[shushes]

1177
01:16:47.478 --> 01:16:49.689
- I made a lot of noise.
- It's okay.

1178
01:16:49.772 --> 01:16:50.857
[grunts]

1179
01:16:50.940 --> 01:16:53.401
No! No! No!

1180
01:16:53.484 --> 01:16:55.611
[both screaming]

1181
01:16:56.904 --> 01:16:58.448
[grunting]

1182
01:16:59.949 --> 01:17:01.951
[sirens blaring]

1183
01:17:07.623 --> 01:17:10.001
[grunting]

1184
01:17:10.084 --> 01:17:11.252
[grunts]

1185
01:17:11.336 --> 01:17:13.254
No! No!

1186
01:17:14.464 --> 01:17:15.465
Get off me!

1187
01:17:16.466 --> 01:17:18.176
Let go!

1188
01:17:18.259 --> 01:17:20.011
- [grunting]
- [man groans]

1189
01:17:21.763 --> 01:17:23.473
[both grunt]

1190
01:17:23.556 --> 01:17:25.725
- [Rachel grunts]
- Mom!

1191
01:17:26.893 --> 01:17:27.727
- No!
- [growls]

1192
01:17:29.437 --> 01:17:30.396
Mom!

1193
01:17:32.565 --> 01:17:34.400
[growling]

1194
01:17:36.402 --> 01:17:37.779
[Rachel yells]

1195
01:17:37.862 --> 01:17:39.072
[both panting]

1196
01:17:51.376 --> 01:17:53.419
- No! No!
- [grunts]

1197
01:17:56.714 --> 01:17:58.341
[choking]

1198
01:17:58.424 --> 01:18:00.426
♪♪

1199
01:18:10.686 --> 01:18:11.521
Hey!

1200
01:18:12.522 --> 01:18:14.107
- [screams]
- [grunts]

1201
01:18:15.691 --> 01:18:17.944
- [groans]
- [gasping]

1202
01:18:21.531 --> 01:18:24.617
[growling]

1203
01:18:24.700 --> 01:18:27.078
Here's your fucking courtesy tap!
[screams]

1204
01:18:31.833 --> 01:18:33.626
[both panting]

1205
01:18:33.709 --> 01:18:35.128
[distant sirens approaching]

1206
01:18:36.212 --> 01:18:37.505
You're okay. You're okay.

1207
01:18:39.715 --> 01:18:41.509
Mom.

1208
01:18:41.592 --> 01:18:43.594
♪♪

1209
01:18:56.691 --> 01:19:00.862
[reporter] <i>We understand that it may have
started as a result of a two-car crash...</i>

1210
01:19:00.945 --> 01:19:02.196
[indistinct chatter]

1211
01:19:03.531 --> 01:19:05.533
♪♪

1212
01:19:23.551 --> 01:19:24.635
[officer] Ms. Flynn?

1213
01:19:25.636 --> 01:19:26.971
May I have a moment?

1214
01:19:28.848 --> 01:19:32.351
It's okay. I'll be right back. Okay?

1215
01:19:34.562 --> 01:19:37.315
I'm so sorry... [continues. inaudible]

1216
01:19:37.398 --> 01:19:39.400
♪♪

1217
01:19:52.497 --> 01:19:53.789
Uncle Fred's alive.

1218
01:19:55.291 --> 01:19:56.375
He is?

1219
01:19:57.376 --> 01:19:58.711
He's gonna be okay.

1220
01:19:58.794 --> 01:20:02.215
- Can we go see him?
- Yeah. Yeah.

1221
01:20:02.298 --> 01:20:04.926
We got your statement.
so you are free to go.

1222
01:20:05.009 --> 01:20:07.011
♪♪

1223
01:20:48.177 --> 01:20:49.303
[brakes squeal]

1224
01:20:49.387 --> 01:20:50.638
[gasps]

1225
01:20:50.721 --> 01:20:51.973
[man] What's your problem?

1226
01:20:52.056 --> 01:20:53.474
[shuddered breathing]

1227
01:21:01.774 --> 01:21:03.234
Good choice.

1228
01:21:05.528 --> 01:21:08.531
["(Don't Fear) The Reaper"
by Keep Shelly In Athens playing]

1229
01:24:21.182 --> 01:24:23.184
♪♪

